announced sweeping new changes in economic policies. Economic Policy Reforms and the Indian Economy evaluates the effects of those changes and identifies areas of the Indian economy still in urgent need of reform. After an overview of Indian economic policies and development since independence, papers focus on the country's fiscal situation, the environment for private economic activity, education, the reservation of certain activities for small-scale industry, and determinants of differentials in rates of growth across the different Indian states. Contributors include respected academic specialists on India and policy reform, high-level Indian administrators, and present and past policymakers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEducation and statexCongressesxIndia. 0aEducation and statezIndiavCongresses. 0aFiscal policyxCongressesxIndia. 0aFiscal policyzIndiavCongresses. 0aIndustrial policyxCongressesxIndia. 0aIndustrial policyzIndiavCongresses. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh  aindia, regional, southeast, asia, eastern, international, global, economy, economics, political, policies, change, 1940s, 1950s, 1960s, 1970s, 1980s, per capita, income, wealth, finance, financial, wages, poverty, growth, expansion, government, independence, academic, scholarly, research, policymaker, differential, liberal, schools, evaluation.1 aAhluwalia, Montek S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChinoy, Sajjid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForbes, Naushad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoster, Andrew D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKochar, Anjini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrueger, Anne O., econtributor.4ctb4ht